<h1>Dropdowns</h1>
<p>Dropdown is toggleable, contextual menu for displaying additional content, mostly for lists of links.</p>

<section>
	<h2>Dropdown composition</h2>
	<p>Dropdown component consists of 3 elements:</p>
	<ul class="wds-list">
		<li>
			- dropdown container (wraps dropdown toggle and dropdown content):
			{{#component-demo codeOnly=true}}
<div class="wds-dropdown">
	<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">...</div>
	<div class="wds-dropdown__content">...</div>
</div>
			{{/component-demo}}
		</li>
		<li>
			- dropdown toggle:
			{{#component-demo codeOnly=true}}
<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">
	<span>...</span>
	<svg class="wds-icon wds-dropdown__toggle-chevron">
		<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#wds-icons-dropdown" />
	</svg>
</div>
			{{/component-demo}}
		</li>
		<li>
			- dropdown content:
			{{#component-demo codeOnly=true}}
<div class="wds-dropdown__content">
	...
</div>
			{{/component-demo}}
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Default</h2>
	<p>Default dropdown, aligned to left with delicate shadow.</p>
	<div class="wds-dropdown wds-is-active">
		<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">
			<span>Default dropdown aligned to left</span>
			<svg class="wds-icon wds-dropdown__toggle-chevron">
				<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#wds-icons-dropdown" />
			</svg>
		</div>
		<div class="wds-dropdown__content">
			<ul class="wds-list">
				<li>List item 1</li>
				<li>List item 2</li>
				<li>List item 3</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Right aligned variant</h2>
	<p>
		Dropdown aligned to the right side of the container.<br/>
		To right align dropdown, you have to add <code>wds-is-right-aligned</code> class to <code>wds-dropdown__content</code> element.
	</p>
	<div class="wds-dropdown wds-is-active">
		<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">
			<span>Right aligned dropdown</span>
			<svg class="wds-icon wds-dropdown__toggle-chevron">
				<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#wds-icons-dropdown" />
			</svg>
		</div>
		<div class="wds-dropdown__content wds-is-right-aligned">
			<ul class="wds-list">
				<li>List item 1</li>
				<li>List item 2</li>
				<li>List item 3</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Dark variant</h2>
	<p>
		Dropdown with increased shadow intensity.<br/>
		To increase dropdown shadow intensity, you have to add <code>wds-is-dark</code> class to <code>wds-dropdown__content</code> element.
	</p>
	<div class="wds-dropdown wds-is-active">
		<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">
			<span>Dark variant of dropdown</span>
			<svg class="wds-icon wds-dropdown__toggle-chevron">
				<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#wds-icons-dropdown" />
			</svg>
		</div>
		<div class="wds-dropdown__content wds-is-dark">
			<ul class="wds-list">
				<li>List item 1</li>
				<li>List item 2</li>
				<li>List item 3</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Demo</h2>
	{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
		{{#dropdown.toggle}}
			<span>Click me!</span>
		{{/dropdown.toggle}}
		{{#dropdown.content}}
			<ul class="wds-list">
				<li>List item 1</li>
				<li>List item 2</li>
				<li>List item 3</li>
			</ul>
		{{/dropdown.content}}
	{{/wds-dropdown}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Example</h2>
	<p>To use this code you have to have Design System's styles and icons.</p>
	{{#component-demo codeOnly=true}}
<div class="wds-dropdown">
	<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">
		<span>Example 1</span>
		<svg class="wds-icon wds-dropdown__toggle-chevron">
			<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#wds-icons-dropdown" />
		</svg>
	</div>
	<div class="wds-dropdown__content">
		<ul class="wds-list">
			<li>List item 1</li>
			<li>List item 2</li>
			<li>List item 3</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>
